                            <comment id="215587" author="jgmitter" created="Thu, 7 Dec 2017 18:34:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch is back ported and appears in Sonia&apos;s comment above.  Is anything else needed here?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="214185" author="sharmaso" created="Mon, 20 Nov 2017 20:54:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is the link to the patch for -&lt;del&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5718&quot; title=&quot;RDMA too fragmented with router&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-5718&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-5718&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/del&gt;- added to b2_8_fe. It still needs to be tested and reviewed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/30184/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/30184/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please note it needs to be accompanied by the fix from -&lt;del&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9420&quot; title=&quot;Bad Check slipped into repo&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-9420&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-9420&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/del&gt;&#160;and &lt;del&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9425&quot; title=&quot;Turn RDMA Fragment Fix on by default&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-9425&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-9425&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/del&gt;-. Backported patch for these -&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/30185/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/30185/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/30284/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/30284/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="214042" author="bhoagland" created="Fri, 17 Nov 2017 18:22:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Amir,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can you help with this one?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Brad&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="213970" author="ofaaland" created="Thu, 16 Nov 2017 23:08:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I can&apos;t figure out how to Link this ticket to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5718&quot; title=&quot;RDMA too fragmented with router&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-5718&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-5718&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; so am noting that here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="213969" author="ofaaland" created="Thu, 16 Nov 2017 23:05:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We see this in Lustre: Build Version: 2.8.0_8.chaos.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One of our larger clusters (~2600 clients) was moved to Lustre 2.8 recently.&#160; We expect to see many more instances of this based on the frequency we see on a small (~128 client) test cluster.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The first question is whether the patch mentioned, &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/12451/12&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/12451/12&lt;/a&gt; is the complete fix for this, or whether other patches are required.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The second question is whether this is a low risk backport (it seems to me that it is, but you would know better).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
